SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA REQUIRE THE TRUSTEES OF THE PLAN TO EVALUATE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE PLAN AND RECOGNIZE A TAX LIABILITY FOR ANY UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE IRS. THE PLAN IS SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDITS BY TAX AUTHORITIES; HOWEVER THERE ARE CURRENTLY NO AUDITS FOR ANY TAX YEARS IN PROGRESS. THE TRUSTEES OF THE PLAN BELIEVE THAT THE PLAN IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS FOR YEARS PRIOR TO FEBRUARY 28, 2014.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PART VII, SECTION A, COLUMN E AND F: THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES APPROVES THE SALARY AND ANY INCREASE ANNUALLY FOR THE FUND MANAGER. THE FUND MANAGER'S SALARY IS PAID BY THE RELATED TEAMSTERS LOCAL UNION NO. 727 PENSION FUND (PENSION FUND) AND IS SHARED WITH THE THE RELATED TEAMSTERS LOCAL UNION NO. 727 LEGAL AND EDUCATIONAL ASSISTANCE FUND (LEGAL AND EDUCATION FUND) AND TEAMSTERS LOCAL UNION NO. 727 HEALTH AND WELFARE FUND (REPORTING FUND). TOTAL COMPENSATION FOR THE FUND MANAGER IS ALLOCATED BETWEEN THESE RELATED BENEFIT FUNDS. TOTAL ALLOCATED COMPENSATION FOR THE FUND MANAGER TO THE REPORTING FUND IS INCLUDED IN PART IX, LINE 5. THE PENSION FUND PAYS CARL TOMINBERG AND GREG YOUMANS FOR SERVICES PROVIDED TO THE RELATED FUNDS. THE COMPENSATION IS ALLOCATED AMONG THE REPORTING FUND, PENSION FUND AND LEGAL AND EDUCATION FUND. TOTAL ALLOCATED COMPENSATION TO THE REPORTING FUND IS INCLUDED IN PART IX, LINE 5.
